'''美洲河狸'''（學名：''Castor canadensis''，英語：North American beaver），又稱'''北美河狸'''，是[[河狸科|河狸科]][[河狸屬|河狸屬]]的一種，是原生於[[北美洲|北美洲]]的[[齧齒目|齧齒動物]]，但現已被引進[[南美|南美]][[巴塔哥尼亞|巴塔哥尼亞]]及[[歐洲|歐洲]]部分地區。在北美洲，本物種通常直接稱為“'''河狸'''”，其他名字，如'''美國河狸''' （American beaver）和'''加拿大河狸'''（Canadian beaver）等名字是要和和分布在歐洲的[[歐亞河狸|歐亞河狸]]區分。美洲河狸是[[加拿大|加拿大]]國家象徵動物及[[俄勒岡州|俄勒岡州]]的州代表動物。

其[[种加词|种加词]]“''canadensis''”意为“[[加拿大|加拿大]]的”。

== 特徵 ==
[[File:Beaver_skeleton.jpg|缩略图]]展示的美洲河狸骨架]]
美洲河狸是北美洲最大的齧齒動物，比歐洲的物種還要來得大得多，兩者皆是北美洲和歐洲最大的齧齒動物，唯南美洲的[[水豚|水豚]]比兩者河狸物種更大。有時歐亞河狸的體型會比美洲河狸大一點，但美洲河狸通常有著比歐洲物種更大的體型。成年重量通常約 {{Convert|11|to|32|kg|lbs|abbr=on}}公斤， {{Convert|20|kg|lbs|abbr=on}}公斤為平均。在[[紐約|紐約]]的成年雄性河狸的體重平均則約 {{Convert|18.9|kg|lb|abbr=on}}公斤， 而非當地物種的[[芬蘭|芬蘭]]的成年雌性平均約 {{Convert|18.1|kg|lb|abbr=on}}公斤。然而在[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]的河狸體重平均約{{Convert|16.8|kg|lb|abbr=on}}公斤<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Pair formation, duration of pair-bonds, and mate replacement in a population of beavers (Castor canadensis)|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_canadian-journal-of-zoology_1989-02_67_2/page/336|last=Svendsen G. E.|journal=Canadian Journal of Zoology|issue=2|doi=10.1139/z89-049|year=1989|volume=67|pages=336–340}}</ref>。本物種因遵照了[[伯格曼法則|伯格曼法則]]，在北方的河狸較南方得大。美洲河狸的體型平均略小於歐洲物種從頭部到尾部的長度約74~90釐米 (29-35英吋) 尾巴可長到 20~35釐米(7.9-13.8英吋)。甚至也有紀錄到 {{Convert|50|kg|lbs|abbr=on}} 公斤重的河狸。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Home Page, Alaska Department of Fish and Game|url=http://www.adfg.state.ak.us/pubs/notebook/furbear/beaver.php|accessdate=2013-03-16|publisher=Adfg.state.ak.us|archive-date=2010-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101124075456/http://www.adfg.state.ak.us/pubs/notebook/furbear/beaver.php|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Burnie">Burnie D and Wilson DE (Eds.), ''Animal: The Definitive Visual Guide to the World's Wildlife''. DK Adult (2005), {{ISBN|0789477645}}</ref>

美洲河狸是[[半水生|半水生]]的，它具有許多適合這種生活方式的特徵，有一個大而扁平的鰭狀尾巴，和較大的蹼狀後腳。未開蹼的前爪較小並內含具爪。前爪具有很高的靈巧性，既可用於挖掘，又可將單片葉子折疊到嘴裡，並在啃樹皮時旋轉細小的鉛筆狀樹柄。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Beaver (Castor canadensis)|url=https://www.aphis.usda.gov/wildlife_damage/beaver_damage/downloads/Baker%20and%20Hill%20Beaver%20Chapter.pdf|last=Baker|first=B.W.|last2=Hill|first2=E.P.|date=2003|journal=Wild Mammals of North America: Biology, Management, and Conservation|publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press|editor-last=Feldhammer|location=Baltimore, Maryland, USA|edition=Second|pages=288–310|access-date=2020-06-09|archive-date=2020-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200123132507/https://www.aphis.usda.gov/wildlife_damage/beaver_damage/downloads/Baker%20and%20Hill%20Beaver%20Chapter.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>眼睛有[[瞬膜|瞬膜]]包覆著，這樣河狸就能在水下看到物體。浸泡當時鼻孔和耳朵密合時，其唇部可在前牙後面閉合，以便繼續在水下呼吸。<ref name=":5">{{Cite book|last=Müller-Schwarze|first=Dietland|title=The beaver : natural history of a wetlands engineer|last2=Sun|first2=Lixing|date=2003|publisher=Cornell University Press|isbn=0-8014-4098-X|location=|pages=10–11|oclc=977989893}}</ref>河狸有一層[[皮下組織|很厚的脂肪在皮下]]， 能在寒冷的水下環境保持暖和。

美洲河狸的[[毛皮|毛皮]]由長而粗的外毛和短而細的內毛組成，功用就像狗的毛髮。毛皮顏色深淺不一，但通常是深褐色。生殖器附近的[[氣味腺|氣味腺]]分泌一種油性物質，稱為[[海狸香|海狸香]]，海狸用這物質來將自己毛皮套上防水。 還有另一組油腺以蠟狀酯及脂肪酸形式產生獨特的化學標識符。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Beaver (Castor canadensis)|url=https://www.aphis.usda.gov/wildlife_damage/beaver_damage/downloads/Baker%20and%20Hill%20Beaver%20Chapter.pdf|last=Baker|first=B.W.|last2=Hill|first2=E.P.|date=2003|journal=Wild Mammals of North America: Biology, Management, and Conservation|publisher=The Johns Hopkins University Press|editor-last=Feldhammer|location=Baltimore, Maryland, USA|edition=Second|pages=288–310}}</ref>其毛皮可加工於皮草，並被製成多種產品及裝飾品，從前就曾因受上層階級對毛皮做成帽子的需求，驅使美洲河狸接近滅絕，使得當時美洲河狸的分布出現變化，分布一度狹窄制局部地方，在數量減少至成瀕臨滅絕物種前，海狸在北美幾乎無處不在，在[[北極|北極]]的[[苔原|苔原]]上，到[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]北部的沙漠，再到[[大西洋|大西洋]]到[[太平洋|太平洋]]沿岸都曾有分布。<ref>{{Cite book|title=The American Beaver and his Works|last=Morgan, Lewis H.|year=1868|publisher=J. B. Lippincott & Co.|page=[https://archive.org/details/americanbeavera00morggoog/page/n43 32]|url=https://archive.org/details/americanbeavera00morggoog}}</ref><ref name="Naiman">{{Cite journal|title=Alteration of North American Streams by Beaver|url=http://www.landscouncil.org/documents/Beaver_Project/Articles/Naiman_et_al_1988_alter_n_american_streams_by_beaver.pdf|last=Naiman, Robert J.|last2=Johnston, Carol A.|date=Dec 1988|journal=BioScience|accessdate=2010-02-28|issue=11|doi=10.2307/1310784|volume=38|pages=753–762|jstor=1310784|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035814/http://www.landscouncil.org/documents/Beaver_Project/Articles/Naiman_et_al_1988_alter_n_american_streams_by_beaver.pdf|archivedate=2012-03-04|last3=Kelley, James C.|lastauthoramp=yes}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The historical range of beaver (Castor canadensis) in coastal California: an updated review of the evidence|url=https://nrm.dfg.ca.gov/FileHandler.ashx?DocumentID=78258|last=Christopher W. Lanman|last2=Kate Lundquist|journal=California Fish and Game|accessdate=2016-09-27|year=2013|volume=99|pages=193–221|last3=Heidi Perryman|last4=J. Eli Asarian|last5=Brock Dolman|last6=Richard B. Lanman|first6=Richard B. Lanman|last7=Michael M. Pollock|number=4|archive-date=2016-10-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161002152319/https://nrm.dfg.ca.gov/FileHandler.ashx?DocumentID=78258|dead-url=no}}</ref>自然博物學家[[埃德加·亞歷山大·梅恩斯|埃德加·亞歷山大·梅恩斯]]（Edgar Alexander Mearns）在1907年在[[索諾拉河|索諾拉河]]發現海狸的報告可能是該北美水生哺乳動物最南端的最早通報。<ref>{{Cite book|title=Mammals of the Mexican boundary of the United States: A descriptive catalogue of the species of mammals occurring in that region; with a general summary of the natural history, and a list of trees|last=Mearns, Edgar Alexander|page=[https://archive.org/details/mammalsmexicanb00meargoog/page/n398 359]|publisher=Government Printing Office|year=1907|url=https://archive.org/details/mammalsmexicanb00meargoog}}</ref>然而，在[[墨西哥|墨西哥]][[索諾拉州|索諾拉州]]、[[奇瓦瓦州|奇瓦瓦州]]、[[科羅拉多河|科羅拉多河]]、[[巴維斯佩河|巴維斯佩河]]和[[聖貝納迪諾河|聖貝納迪諾河]]都曾通報有分布。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Status of Beavers (''Castor canadensis frontador'') in Rio Bavispe, Sonora, Mexico|url=https://ciad.academia.edu/JuanPabloGallo/Papers/590136/Status_of_beavers_Castor_canadensis_frondator_in_Rio_Bavispe_Sonora_Mexico|last=Gallo-Reynoso, Juan-Pablo|last2=Suarez-Gracida, Gabriela|date=2002|journal=The Southwestern Naturalist|accessdate=2011-11-25|issue=3|doi=10.2307/3672516|volume=47|pages=501|jstor=3672516|last3=Cabrera-Santiago, Horacia|last4=Coria-Galindo, Else|last5=Egido-Villarreal, Janitzio|last6=Ortiz, Leo C.|lastauthoramp=yes|archive-date=2021-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211122045346/https://www.academia.edu/587131/Status_of_beavers_Castor_canadensis_frondator_in_Rio_Bavispe_Sonora_Mexico|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Habitat and Conservation Status of the Beaver in the Sierra San Luis Sonora, México|url=https://www.fs.fed.us/rm/pubs/rmrs_p036/rmrs_p036_429_433.pdf|last=Karla Pelz Serrano|last2=Eduardo Ponce Guevara|journal=USDA Forest Service Proceedings RMRS-P-36|accessdate=2017-12-05|last3=Carlos A. López González|archive-date=2017-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170505154944/https://www.fs.fed.us/rm/pubs/rmrs_p036/rmrs_p036_429_433.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Nice surprise: camera discovers that there are otters in Chihuahua|author=El Heraldo de Chihuahua|work=El Sol de Mexico|date=2017-12-05|url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/doble-via/ecologia/bonita-sorpresa-camara-descubre-que-hay-nutrias-en-chihuahua-385554.html|accessdate=2020-06-09|archive-date=2020-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200804214743/https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/doble-via/ecologia/bonita-sorpresa-camara-descubre-que-hay-nutrias-en-chihuahua-385554.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

美洲河狸會一直不停長[[門牙|門牙]]，會在有木質的樹木上磨牙縮減門牙長度，並且也有後腸發酵作用，其[[盲腸|盲腸]]裡有很多共生細菌，有助於消化植物性物質。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Dental Anatomy of Rodents|url=http://www.vivo.colostate.edu/hbooks/pathphys/digestion/pregastric/rodentpage.html|accessdate=2020-02-21|work=www.vivo.colostate.edu|archive-date=2019-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716194558/http://www.vivo.colostate.edu/hbooks/pathphys/digestion/pregastric/rodentpage.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>海狸非常專門地有效消化於富含[[木質纖維素|木質纖維素]]的食物。<ref name=":6">{{Cite journal|title=Bacterial and Archaeal Diversity in the Gastrointestinal Tract of the North American Beaver (Castor canadensis)|last=Gruninger|first=Robert J.|last2=McAllister|first2=Tim A.|date=2016-05-26|journal=PLOS ONE|issue=5|doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0156457|volume=11|pages=e0156457|issn=1932-6203|pmc=4881982|pmid=27227334|last3=Forster|first3=Robert J.}}</ref>

大腦解剖學顯示河狸並不是那麼地演化成完全適應地其半水生生活，某些時候大部分活動是在陸上。海狸的體重為11.7和17千克，分別為41和45克。美洲河狸與其他囓齒類相比，其[[腦化指數|腦化指數]]為0.9； 介於部分陸生囓齒類和樹棲[[松鼠|松鼠]]之間，高於部分的水陸囓齒類，[[麝鼠|麝鼠]]和[[海狸鼠|海狸鼠]]。顯示美洲河狸的[[大腦|大腦]]有少許程度的發展，[[新皮質|新皮質]]較大。美洲河狸的[[體感|體感]]皮層的較大區域用於處理唇部和手部的刺激，作用比尾巴和鬍來的重要，後者的作用相對較小，大腦的視覺區域則比[[灰松鼠|灰松鼠]]小。<ref name=":5">{{Cite book|last=Müller-Schwarze|first=Dietland|title=The beaver : natural history of a wetlands engineer|last2=Sun|first2=Lixing|date=2003|publisher=Cornell University Press|isbn=0-8014-4098-X|location=|pages=10–11|oclc=977989893}}</ref>

