== 與人類的關係 ==
=== 保護狀態及生態角色 ===
美洲河狸在過去曾因其皮毛和身上獨特的香而被大量獵殺，其皮毛更用來製作衣服及帽子，使得美洲河狸直到20世紀前處在瀕臨絕種的狀態，甚至銳減至只剩數千隻左右，一度接近滅絕邊緣。<ref name="Naiman">{{Cite journal|title=Alteration of North American Streams by Beaver|url=http://www.landscouncil.org/documents/Beaver_Project/Articles/Naiman_et_al_1988_alter_n_american_streams_by_beaver.pdf|last=Naiman, Robert J.|last2=Johnston, Carol A.|date=Dec 1988|journal=BioScience|accessdate=2010-02-28|issue=11|doi=10.2307/1310784|volume=38|pages=753–762|jstor=1310784|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304035814/http://www.landscouncil.org/documents/Beaver_Project/Articles/Naiman_et_al_1988_alter_n_american_streams_by_beaver.pdf|archivedate=2012-03-04|last3=Kelley, James C.|lastauthoramp=yes}}</ref>誘捕狩獵法在17世紀初美國開始廣泛的運用，每年在1620至1630年間在[[康涅狄格州|康涅狄格州]]和[[馬薩諸塞州|馬薩諸塞州]]進行[[皮草貿易|皮草貿易]]的河狸超過10,000隻。從1630年至1640年，每年從[[哈德遜河|哈德遜河]]約80,000隻河狸被捕抓。<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Fur Trade in New England, 1620–1676|last=Moloney, F. X.|year=1967|publisher=Archon Books|location=Hamden, Connecticut|page=150}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Notes on the range of some of the animals in America at the time of arrival of the whitemen|last=Hays, W. J.|date=September 1871|journal=The American Naturalist|issue=7|doi=10.1086/270797|volume=5|pages=25–30|jstor=2447602|subscription=free}}</ref>1670年後[[哈德遜灣公司|哈德遜灣公司]]每年都會派兩三艘商船進入該海灣，從加拿大將皮草運到英國。考古和歷史證據表明，河狸棲息的河岸邊在北美東部的落葉林中出現了很多“蛾洞狀”棲息地。 這片河岸、非森林的空地吸引了早期殖民地獵人、農民及[[美洲原住民|美洲原住民]]，他們就此在該地定居。這裡積聚的淤泥和有機物所聚積而成的肥沃平坦的平原，吸引了許多人來到這裡狩獵大量豐富的魚類，水禽和大型獵物，及被肥沃的土地和豐盛的食物吸引的水生哺乳動物。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=''Home sapiens'' or ''Castor fiber''?|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_antiquity_1983-07_57_220/page/95|last=Coles, J. M.|last2=Orme, B. J.|journal=Antiquity|issue=220|doi=10.1017/S0003598X00055265|year=1983|volume=57|pages=95–102}}</ref>

隨著東部河狸種群消滅殆盡，獵人們轉移到西部狩獵。對北美動物皮毛的大部分向西擴張和探索都是由於對河狸皮毛的追求所致。在1849年[[加利福尼亞淘金潮|加利福尼亞淘金潮]]前，更早的19世紀[[加利福尼亞毛皮潮|加利福尼亞毛皮潮]]推動了該州最早的美國移民潮。在大約32年（1806-1838年）的[[山地人_(美國)|山地人]]時期中，從密蘇里州到加利福尼亞州、加拿大到墨西哥的西部地區被的河狸被徹底大量消滅。

在19世紀末和20世紀初受到保護後，目前的美洲河狸數量已回升至現時估計的1000至1500萬隻。 數量少於開始皮草貿易前10倍，約1至2億隻。<ref>Seton-Thompson, cited in {{Cite book|last=Sun|first=Lixing|last2=Müller-Schwarze, Dietland|title=The Beaver: Natural History of a Wetlands Engineer|publisher=Cornell University Press|year=2003|location=Ithaca, NY|pages=97–98|url=https://books.google.com/?id=eqIenKko3lAC|isbn=978-0-8014-4098-4}}; but note that to arrive at this figure he assumed a population density throughout the range equivalent to that in [[阿尔冈金省立公园|Algonquin Park]]</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=Water:A Natural History|last=Outwater, Alice|publisher=Basic Books|year=1997|location=New York, NY|page=89|isbn=978-0-465-03780-3|url=https://books.google.com/?id=3_oRrNgE_mkC}}</ref>
[[File:Beavers_Ain't_Chopping_That_Tree_Down_(4340897705).jpg|缩略图]]安裝的鐵絲網籬芭。使用金屬絲網圍欄以防止該樹木被河狸啃壞。<ref name="mesh">{{Cite web|title=Trees in parks & ravines - beavers|url=https://www.toronto.ca/311/knowledgebase/kb/docs/articles/parks,-forestry-and-recreation/urban-forestry/trees-in-parks-and-ravines-beavers.html|accessdate=2019-07-29|year=2018|work=311 Toronto|publisher=City of Toronto|archive-date=2020-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200805000616/https://www.toronto.ca/311/knowledgebase/kb/docs/articles/parks,-forestry-and-recreation/urban-forestry/trees-in-parks-and-ravines-beavers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>]]
美洲河狸在一些區域被認為是[[害獸|害獸]]，因為它們的水壩會引起洪水，或者會對他們砍伐樹木的習俗構成危險或騷擾。<ref>{{Cite web|title=South Charlotte Weekly: Beavers damaging Park Road Park; must go|url=http://www.thecharlotteweekly.com/news/2012/03/county-beavers-damaging-park-road-park-must-go/|author=Parks, Mike|date=2012-03-01|publisher=Thecharlotteweekly.com|access-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307073310/http://www.thecharlotteweekly.com/news/2012/03/county-beavers-damaging-park-road-park-must-go/|archive-date=2012-03-07|dead-url=yes}}</ref>由於這些因素，美洲河狸在歷史上曾因此被在這些區域遭強制驅離或滅絕。然而隨著環境保育意識出現，不合時宜的舊有驅離法被淘汰，新方法必須要採用對環境友善並且也能驅離河狸的效果為原則，不僅能驅離也不會傷害它更也能改善環境<ref>{{Cite web|title=Beavers: Wetlands & Wildlife: Solutions to Beaver/Human Conflicts|url=http://www.beaversww.org/solutions.html|accessdate=2013-03-16|publisher=Beaversww.org|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080220213900/http://www.beaversww.org/solutions.html|archivedate=2008-02-20}}</ref>。例如由野生動物學家史基普‧利斯勒（Skip Lisle）發明，被稱為“河狸欺騙器”的調整流量[[矯直機|矯直機]]。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Beaver Deceiver expert coming to Pitkin County|author=Agar, Charles|work=The Aspen Times|location=Aspen, Colorado|date=2008-03-24|url=http://www.aspentimes.com/article/20080324/NEWS/47844491|accessdate=2009-11-22|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100118013957/http://www.aspentimes.com/article/20080324/NEWS/47844491|archivedate=2010-01-18}}</ref>

美洲河狸是北美生態的[[基石物種|基石物種]]，通過建立池子和濕地來增加其棲息地上的生物多樣性。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=An ecosystem engineer, the beaver, increases species richness at the landscape scale|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_oecologia_2002-06_132_1/page/96|last=Wright, J.P.|last2=Jones, C.G.|journal=Oecologia|issue=1|doi=10.1007/s00442-002-0929-1|year=2002|volume=132|pages=96–101|bibcode=2002Oecol.132...96W|pmid=28547281|last3=Flecker, A.S.}}</ref>隨著濕地的形成和河岸生態系的擴大，水生植物會擴散至新的水陸中。 各種生物的多樣性也因河狸建造水壩擴大棲息地範圍而受惠。<ref name="Rosell">{{Cite journal|title=Ecological impact of beavers ''Castor fiber'' and ''Castor canadensis'' and their ability to modify ecosystems|url=http://teora.hit.no/dspace/bitstream/2282/536/1/Ecological_impact.pdf|last=Rosell F|last2=Bozser O|journal=Mammal Review|accessdate=2010-03-01|issue=3–4|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2907.2005.00067.x|year=2005|volume=35|pages=248–276|last3=Collen P|last4=Parker H|archive-date=2012-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120304003304/http://teora.hit.no/dspace/bitstream/2282/536/1/Ecological_impact.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

