在紐約，河狸在當地消失長達200年後，於2007年在紐約市現身，便在此地住下來，並在[[布朗克斯動物園|布朗克斯動物園]]和[[布朗克斯植物園|植物園]]裡度過了一段時間後離開，這隻河狸的名字以布朗克斯市議員[[何塞·塞拉諾|何塞·塞拉諾]]（José Serrano）的名字命名為“何塞”， 河狸皮曾對紐約經濟很重要，並且有一對河狸出現在該市的印章和國旗上，但從19世紀初被獵人獵殺殆盡之後到上述段落河狸現身之事件前，河狸一直在該地滅絕，何塞的回歸被視為紐約河川整治成功的證據。<ref>{{Cite news|title=New York City Beaver Returns|work=Science Daily|url=https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/12/081218080817.htm|date=2008-12-20|accessdate=2020-06-09|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609142539/https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2008/12/081218080817.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Manhattan Before New York: When Henry Hudson first looked on Manhattan in 1609, what did he see?|url=http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2009/09/manhattan/miller-text|last=Miller, Peter|date=September 2009|journal=National Geographic|access-date=2020-06-09|archive-date=2018-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180317011706/http://ngm.nationalgeographic.com/2009/09/manhattan/miller-text|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=After 200 Years, a Beaver Is Back in New York City|author=O'Connor, Anahad|work=The New York Times|date=2007-02-23|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/23/nyregion/23beaver.html?_r=1|accessdate=2009-12-04|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609153408/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/23/nyregion/23beaver.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Bronx River Crossing|url=http://designtrust.blogspot.com/2009/06/bronx-river-crossing.html|accessdate=2009-12-04|author=Design Trust for Public Space|date=2009-06-17|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609142542/http://designtrust.blogspot.com/2009/06/bronx-river-crossing.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>2010年夏天紐約出現了第二隻河狸，命名為“賈斯汀” ，兩隻河狸在2013年2月被動態感應相機觀測到在[[紐約植物園|紐約植物園]]活動。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Another beaver makes Bronx River home – doubles total beaver population|author=Paddock, Barry|work=Daily News|location=New York|date=2010-09-19|url=